Definition: An acronym is an abbreviation formed from the initial letters of other words and pronounced as a word (e.g. ASCII, NASA). This task is about reading the given pre-tokenized sentence which may contain a token as an acronym and output 'Yes' to indicate that the sentence contains an acronym or output 'No' to indicate that the sentence does not contain an acronym.
